When the select2 is opened (clicked), the `.select2-container--open` class gets `z-index: 9999 !important`. This makes the select2 container jump to a very high z-index, which is why the label (which has no explicit z-index) goes "behind" the select2 container.

The fix is to add `z-index` to the `.label-flotante` when it's in the floated (top) position, so it appears on top of the select2-container even when it has `z-index: 9999`.


The real issue is that the `z-index: 9999` applies to the entire select2 container, not just the dropdown portion—it was probably added to prevent the dropdown from being hidden behind modals or other overlays. I need to either give the label a higher z-index when it's floated at the top, or find a way to apply the high z-index only to the dropdown part itself. The safer approach is to add a z-index to the label when it's in its floated state, which means I need to find where that styling gets applied when select2 is focused or open.

